This guide describes the <%= vars.product_full %>, which secures data transmissions inside [<%= vars.platform_name %>](https://network.pivotal.io/products/pivotal-cf). Topics covered in this guide include <%= vars.product_full %> installation and configuration, troubleshooting, and certificate rotation.

Your org might require <%= vars.product_short %> if you transmit sensitive data.

## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

<%= vars.product_full %> provides security to the network layer of the OSI model with a
[strongSwan](https://www.strongswan.org/) implementation of <%= vars.product_short %>.
<%= vars.product_short %> provides a strongSwan job in FIPS mode to each BOSH-deployed VM.

<%= vars.product_short %> encrypts IP data flow between hosts, between security gateways, between service tiles, and between security gateways and hosts.
<%= vars.product_full %> secures network traffic within a Cloud Foundry deployment
and provides internal system protection if a malicious actor breaches your firewall.

